<title>USA: American Diversified chairman resigns.</title>
<headline>American Diversified chairman resigns.</headline>
<dateline>WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. 1996-11-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>American Diversified Group Inc said Tuesday that its chairman, Gerard Haryman, has announced his resignation.</p>
<p>The company said Haryman told its board that &quot;he wished to devote more of his business time to his private business interests.&quot;</p>
<p>The company said it has not found a successor.</p>
<p>The company said its president and chief executive, Jerrold Hinton, will remain, following board authorization of a new three-year employment pact with Hinton.</p>
